[Maps of Zimbabwe can be seen at http://www.un.org/Depts/Cartographic/map/profile/zimbabwe.pdf and https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=5028820,59888.
For a description of Matabeleland North on the western border of Zimbabwe with Zambia, go to https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Matabeleland_North_Province. Binga District lies along the border with Zimbabwe and the Zambezi River valley; see https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Binga_District. It can be seen on the map at http://tinyurl.com/kkn6l9s.

Unfortunately fresh anthrax deaths beget fresh deaths. Young crocodiles, 3-4 months old, are small, say around 24 inches or 61 cm long, and once dead would be swept downstream from wherever they had died. It was observant of the ZimParks rangers to have found them. Until it is confirmed that they died of anthrax, we must presume that they died of whatever routinely takes young Zim crocodiles in the Zambezi valley ecosystem. And it is comforting to not hear of any further human deaths. - Mod.MHJ]
